page.title: 10LOCAL HISTORY 3
page.content: THE MAN WE TALKED TO WAS IN THIS RAID. A GROUP OF ARMY MEN SET OFF ON A MISSION FOR THE BRITISH TO BLOW UP A MAJOR{GERMAN DOCK. THERE SHIP WAS CARRYING A {GERMAN FLAG,}AND THEY WERE PRETENDING TO BE A GERMAN SHIP. THE SHIP CAME IN THE DOCK AND SUDDENLY THE SECRET SHIP SURPRISED THE GERMANS.CARRYING LOTS OF EXPLOSIVES,THE BRITISH SOLDIERS BLEW UP THE PUMPS 40 FEET DOWN IN THE GROUND. THEY BLEW UP THE GATES TO THE DOCK, AND ALL THE GERMAN SUBMARINES TURNED UPSIDE DOWN AS THE WATER SWEPT OUT OF THE DOCK. THEN THE BRITISH SOLDIERS TORPEDOED EVERYTHING ON THE TOP OF THE DOCK,BLOWING UP{10 MILLION POUNDS}OF EQUIPMENT.
